race.comment: HEAVENLY KISS (5) capped off a solid campaign with a barnstorming win as favourite to shed her maiden tag at Albury on May 16. Readied with a quiet trial and reunites with winning hoop in Boudvillain. Bright return anticipated. MAGIC LEPRECHAUN (3) is ticking along nicely, improved last start but found a couple better over 1000m at Corowa. Kept on the fresh side for this and is nicely placed to play a major role. LUNA JET (8) had excuses when a disappointing favourite at Goulburn when resuming. Is much better than that and can improve sharply. Don't underestimate. ZABELLSARERINGING (4) didn't fire a shot here first-up but it was 530 days between starts. May need another blow out but was a handy type prior to the layoff. Don't dismiss.
